import{_ as t,o,c as r,a as n,d as e,e as s,b as a}from"./app-de7a4551.js";const c={},d=e("h1",{id:"a-mysterious-design-that-appears-across-millennia-3",tabindex:"-1"},[e("a",{class:"header-anchor",href:"#a-mysterious-design-that-appears-across-millennia-3","aria-hidden":"true"},"#"),s(" A Mysterious Design That Appears Across Millennia （3）")],-1),i=a('<p>Clearly there&#39;s an <em><code>underlying</code> structure</em> and unity to things that seem to be complex and <code>aperiodic</code>.</p><p>This <code>notion</code> of a hidden <em>underlying unity</em> was <em>common throughout</em> the ancient world, and one sees it in Egypt, in Greece, in Australia, in Mesoamerica, in North America, in Europe and in the Middle East.</p><p>Now in the modern West, we might call this underlying unity &quot;God,&quot;</p><p>but <em>throughout the ages</em>, other <code>terms</code> have been used to describe the same thing.</p><p>This is what Plato called &quot;first cause.&quot;</p><p>In the <em><code>medieval</code> period</em>, philosopher Spinoza called this the &quot;<code>singular</code> substance.&quot;</p><p>In the 20th century, a number of terms were <code>coined</code> to describe this,</p><p>one of my favorites being from philosopher Alfred North Whitehead, who called this the &quot;<code>undifferentiated</code> <code>aesthetic</code> <code>continuum</code>.&quot;</p><p>Doesn&#39;t that have a 20th century sound to it?</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 显然有一个潜在的结构和统一性，藏在看似复杂、非周期性的事物之下。<br> 这种隐藏的潜在统一性的概念在古代世界屡见不鲜，埃及出现过，希腊出现过，澳大利亚出现过，中美洲出现过，北美出现过，欧洲出现过，中东也出现过。<br> 在当代西方，我们会将这一隐含的统一称为&quot;上帝&quot;，<br> 但长久以来，它也有过其它名称。<br> 柏拉图称之为&quot;第一因&quot;。<br> 中世纪，哲学家斯宾诺莎（Spinoza）称之为&quot;单一物质&quot;。<br> 在20 世纪，出现了很多描述它的词语，<br> 我最喜欢的一个来自哲学家阿弗烈·诺夫·怀特海（Alfred North Whitehead），他称之为&quot;同质美学连续体&quot;。<br> 听起来是不是很 20 世纪？</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> underlying structure -&gt; 潜在的结构/基础结构<br> underlying unity -&gt; 潜在的统一性/基础统一性<br> common throughout -&gt; 遍布全球<br> throughout the ages -&gt; 一直以来/ 自古以来<br> medieval period -&gt; 中世纪</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> underlying<br><code>英 [ˌʌndəˈlaɪɪŋ]美 [ˌʌndərˈlaɪɪŋ]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 根本的，潜在的；表面下的，下层的；优先的；（数量或水平）实际的<br> v. 位于…的下面；构成…的基础（underlie 的现在分词形式）</p></blockquote><p>aperiodic<br><code>英 [ˌeɪpɪərɪˈɒdɪk]美 [ˌeɪˌpɪriˈɑːdɪk]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 不定期的；非周期性的</p></blockquote><p>notion [ 复数 notions ]<br><code>英 [ˈnəʊʃ(ə)n]美 [ˈnoʊʃ(ə)n]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 概念，想法；缝纫用品；一时的念头，突发的奇想</p></blockquote><p>terms ( terming, termed, terms )<br><code>英 [tɜːmz]美 [tɜːrmz]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 地位，关系；[法]条款；术语；措辞；价钱（term 的复数形式）<br> v. 把……称为（term 的三单形式）</p></blockquote><p>medieval<br><code>英 [ˌmediˈiːv(ə)l]美 [ˌmiːdˈiːv(ə)l]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 中世纪的；&lt;非正式&gt;非常老派的，极其过时的</p></blockquote><p>singular<br><code>英 [ˈsɪŋɡjələ(r)]美 [ˈsɪŋɡjələr]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 单数的，单数形式的；&lt;正式&gt;非凡的，突出的；&lt;文&gt;奇怪的，异常的；独一无二的，独特的；（数）（方阵）零行列式的<br> n. 单数，单数形式（the singular）</p></blockquote><p>coined ( coining, coined, coins )<br><code>英 [kɔɪnd]美 [kɔɪnd]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 创造（新词等）；铸造（硬币）（coin 的过去式和过去分词）</p></blockquote><p>undifferentiated<br><code>英 [ˌʌndɪfəˈrenʃieɪtɪd]美 [ˌʌndɪfəˈrenʃieɪtɪd]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 分不开的，无差别的</p></blockquote><p>aesthetic (also esthetic)<br><code>英 [iːsˈθetɪk]美 [esˈθetɪk]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 审美的，美学的；美的，艺术的<br> n. 美感，审美观；美学（aesthetics）；美术理论</p></blockquote><p>continuum<br><code>英 [kənˈtɪnjuəm]美 [kənˈtɪnjuəm]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. [数] 连续统；[经] 连续统一体；闭联集<br> [ 复数 continua或continuums ]</p></blockquote></details><p>But for me, a lover of science that I am,</p><p>I will take the <em>term coined</em> by the great 20th century <code>physicist</code> David Bohm, who called this the &quot;implicate order.&quot;</p><p>So what&#39;s the <code>takeaway</code> here?</p><p>Very simply, this.</p><p>When we see these wonderful designs created by cultures that are <code>separated</code> from our own by thousands of miles or thousands of years, we can know these aren&#39;t decorations.</p><p>These are statements about the <em>fundamental values</em> that culture had, what they found important, how they saw themselves, the world and themselves in the world.</p><p>It has been said that <code>architecture</code> is a book written in stone.</p><p>So when we see these amazing designs, we can know they&#39;re not decorations.</p><p>They&#39;re a statement.</p><p>They&#39;re a message.</p><p>Look, listen. You can hear their voices.</p><p>Thank you.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 但对我这位科学爱好者来说，<br> 我会选取 20 世纪的伟大物理学家戴维·玻姆（David Bohm）创造的术语，称之为&quot;隐序&quot;。<br> 那么今天的要点是什么呢？<br> 很简单。<br> 当看到与我们相距千里、相距千年的文化创造出的精美设计时，我们就知道它们并非只是装饰，<br> 它们呈现了那个文明的基本价值、珍视之物、自我映射、眼里的世界和身处其中的自己。<br> 有人说，建筑物是用石头撰写的书。<br> 当看到这些美丽的设计时，我们就知道它们并不是装饰，<br> 它们是一种声明，<br> 传递一个信息。<br> 看一看，听一听，你能听到他们的声音。<br> 谢谢。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> term coined -&gt; 创造术语<br> fundamental values -&gt; 基本价值</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> physicist [ 复数 physicists ]<br><code>英 [ˈfɪzɪsɪst]美 [ˈfɪzɪsɪst]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 物理学家</p></blockquote><p>takeaway [ 复数 takeaways ]<br><code>英 [ˈteɪkəweɪ]美 [ˈteɪkəweɪ]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 外卖食品；外卖餐馆；要点</p></blockquote><p>separated<br><code>英 [ˈsepəreɪtɪd]美 [ˈsepəreɪtɪd]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 分居的，独居的；脱臼的，脱位的；相距遥远的<br> v. （使）分开，分离；隔开，阻隔；分居（separate 的过去式和过去分词形式）</p></blockquote><p>architecture [ 复数 architectures ]<br><code>英 [ˈɑːkɪtektʃə(r)]美 [ˈɑːrkɪtektʃər]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 建筑设计，建筑风格；建筑学；结构；计算机的体系结构，架构</p></blockquote></details>',23);function p(u,h){return o(),r("div",null,[d,n(" 一个跨越千年的神秘设计(3)  "),i])}const b=t(c,[["render",p],["__file","28-mysterious-design-3.html.vue"]]);export{b as default};
